title: piers_nivans
body:
A young BSAA operative serving under the North American branch's Special Operations Unit Alpha Team, and [[chris_redfield|Chris's]] partner in [[Resident Evil 6]].

Piers Nivans, like his captain Chris Redfield, is a naturally gifted marksman, and has become known as "The man who never misses a target" in the B.S.A.A. He is also a person with a strong sense of responsibility, and is able to influence his teammates into the right course of action on the battlefield.

It's because of these qualities that makes Piers a highly trusted soldier in the B.S.A.A, and Chris regards him as a figure that will lead the B.S.A.A one day.

h4.Appearance
Piers is a [[muscular]] man with [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes]]. He wears a [[brown jacket]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[black pants]], [[boots]], [[brown scarf]] and [[black gloves]].

title: minnan_text
body:
Images that contain text written in Minnan, a branch of Min Chinese spoken in Fujian and Taiwan. Some members of the Chinese diaspora (i.e. Overseas Chinese) in Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia and the Philippines (and also some older members of the Chinese communities in San Francisco, Los Angeles and NYC) may also use a form of Minnan as their mother tongue.

The term [i]Minnan[/i] is generally used to refer to Quanzhang and Zhangzhou variants of Minnan, and descendants thereof. Minnan can also technically refer to other varieties of Southern Min (e.g. Teochew (Chaozhou)), but this use will be excluded for the purposes of this wiki (and tagging on Danbooru).

Speakers of Minnan often have their own preferred way to refer to it: this includes Fujianhua, Fujianese, Fukien, Taigi, Holo, Hokkien, etc. The choice of which term to use can be fraught with... [i]political issues[/i], and as such "Minnan" is frequently used as a more neutral term that most speakers can understand as referring to the Quanzhang and Zhangzhou variants of Minnan (and descendants).

For Danbooru purposes (i.e. considering the demographics of the artists whose works are likely to be uploaded by users), most examples of Minnan text are likely to be in a Taiwanese variant of Minnan. These will usually be written in [[Traditional Chinese Text|Traditional Chinese]] characters (with occasional [[bopomofo_text]]), and mixed in with (sometimes accented) Mandarin Chinese (also written in Traditional Chinese). Minnan written in this way makes frequent use of Chinese characters chosen only for their phonetic values to approximate the pronunciations of Minnan, or to act as euphenisms.

Mainland Chinese artists who write in Minnan are also likely to mix Minnan with Mandarin Chinese (and employ similar euphemisms), but the text will be written in Simplified Chinese characters instead.

Artists from Singapore and Malaysia tend to write in English, but some (particularly those of Chinese descent) may also insert certain Minnan phrases, written using the Latin alphabet. These tend to be profanity. Minnan is... well-known for having a rich vocabulary of colorful phrases.

h4. Notes
* The above article has been written carefully in a certain way to avoid triggering political sensibilities. This may have resulted in the article using language that is less clear than ideal.
** In particular, usage of the... 'D' and 'L' words are avoided.
** The article (and tag) also uses the term Minnan, a more neutral term.
** As such, be careful if one chooses to rewrite or edit this wiki.

h4. Notable artists
* [[Hi Ye]]
** Taiwanese artist.
** Character speech in comics are usually written in Mandarin Chinese (using Traditional Chinese characters). 
** Characters may sometimes switch to accented Mandarin or Minnan in more emotional moments.
** This distinction is lost in the Japanese translations of the comics.

* [[Guin Guin]]
** Malaysian artist.
** Character speech in comics are usually written in English.
** Characters (particularly those of implied Chinese descent) may sometimes insert Minnan phrases (written using the Latin alphabet) in more emotional moments.

h4. Notable examples
* Post #4451091
** All the dialogue is in Minnan. Only exception being the artist's notes.
** Features some of the more colorful phrases.

* Post #4586418
** Entire page is in Minnan. Other than signboard and Japanese SFX.

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Minnan":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Min]
** Has a broader definition of Minnan (to include some other Min Chinese branches).
* "Wikipedia: Hokkien":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hokkien]

title: vladimir_harkonnen
body:
The Baron [b]Vladimir Harkonnen[/b] is a character from the Dune universe created by Frank Herbert. 

He is primarily featured in the 1965 [[science fiction]] novel [i]Dune[/i], in which he is the main antagonist, and is also a major character in the [i]Prelude to Dune[/i] prequel trilogy (1999-2001) by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson. 

The Baron also appears in the Herbert/Anderson sequels which conclude the original series, [i]Hunters of Dune[/i] (2006) and [i]Sandworms of Dune[/i] (2007). He was played by Kenneth McMillan in the 1984 film adaptation of the first novel, and by Ian McNeice in the 2000 miniseries [i]Frank Herbert's Dune[/i] and its 2003 sequel, [i]Frank Herbert's Children of Dune[/i].


Vladimir Harkonnen is the supreme leader of [[House Harkonnen]] based on [[planet]] Giedi Prime. He is so grossly and immensely fat that he requires anti-gravity devices known as "suspensors" to support his weight (hence his nickname, "the floating fatman").

title: feyd-rautha
body:
The na-Baron [b]Feyd-Rautha Harkonnen[/b] is a character and antagonist in the [[science fiction]] novel [[dune (series)|Dune]] by Frank Herbert.

The younger nephew of the cruel, powerful and cunning Baron [[Vladimir Harkonnen]], the young Feyd is as lean and muscular as the Baron is morbidly obese. 

Feyd and his elder brother Glossu Rabban are the legal sons of Baron [[Harkonnen]]'s youngest demibrother, Abulurd Rabban, who had renounced the Harkonnen name and all rights to the title when given the subdistrict governorship of Rabban-Lankiveil.

As Dune begins, Feyd-Rautha figures heavily in the Baron's plans to gain power for [[House Harkonnen]]. The Baron favors the handsome and charismatic Feyd over Feyd's older brother Glossu Rabban ("The Beast") because of Feyd's extreme intelligence and his dedication to the Harkonnen culture of carefully planned and subtly executed sadism and cruelty, as opposed to Rabban's outright brutality.

In the "David Lynch":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Lynch "1984 film adaptation of the novel":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dune_(1984_film) the character was played by the famous musician and ex- "Police" music band member "Sting":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sting_(musician) .

Ayra is a [[black hair|black-haired]] swordswoman from the first generation of [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of The Holy War]]. Ayra holds the honor of being the first Swordmaster in the series, as well as being the first 'true' member of the [[Navarre (Fire Emblem)|]] archetype. She is vehemently protective of her half-nephew [[Shannan (Fire Emblem)|]], the only child of her brother Mariccle, the Isaachian crown prince.

Together with one of several first-generation men, she can have two children: [[Larcei (Fire Emblem)|]], her daughter, who can be told apart from her mother by her shorter hair and dress, as well as her armor having a gold trim; and [[Scathach (fire emblem)|]], her son. Her children are twins.

title: kanojo_no_carrera
body:
A [[car]] focused manga series by [[Kikuchi Michitaka]]. The series follows [[Todoroki Reina]], a woman who initially knows nothing about cars, but plunges headfirst into the world of exotic sports cars upon inheriting her late father's [[porsche 964|964]] [[Porsche 911]].

The series originally ran from 2004 to 2012 and has been followed up with several sequels:

* Kanojo no Carrera RS 0 (2013)
* [[Kanojo no Carrera RS]] (2013 - 2015)
* [[Kanojo no Carrera GT3]] (2018 - present)

In addition to the sequels, the series also had a spinoff manga titled [b]Zero Angel ~Souheki no Datenshi~[/b] that ran from 2016 to 2018.

The original run was later rereleased digitally as [b]Kanojo no Carrera EV[/b]. The first 10 volumes of the rerelease have been licensed and released digitally in English as [b]My Favorite Carrera EV[/b] on "Manga Planet":[https://mangaplanet.com/comic/5dca46af44f90].

title: js_taigei
body:
JS [i]Taigei[/i] (SS-513), the name ship of the [[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force]]'s Taigei-class attack [[submarine]]s. Laid down at the Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Kobe Shipyard, it was named at its launch on October 14, 2020 and is scheduled to be turned over to the Maritime Self-Defense Force in 2022.

News of the submarine's launch prompted fan artists to dress the [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i] [[personification]] of its [[name connection]], [[taigei (kancolle)|a WWII submarine tender]], the same way that game depicts its submarines -- wearing a [[school swimsuit]].

title: pps-43
body:
The [b]PPS-43[/b] (Пистолет-пулемёт Судаева) is a [b][[submachine gun]][/b] chambered in 7.62×25mm Tokarev, developed by Alexei Sudayev as an alternative to the PPSh-41 with lower manufacturing cost and lower rate of fire. The [[gun]] has open-bolt blowback mechanism, predominant sheet metal parts, a pistol grip, and a top-[[folding stock]]. The magazines of both [[weapon]]s are not interchangeable.

The PPS-43 and its variants were used extensively by the Soviet forces during World War II and were later adopted by post-war militaries of several communist/socialist countries.

title: i_am_a_surgeon_(meme)
body:
A meme based on the medical tv show, [[The Good Doctor]] . 

In Season 2, Episode 17 titled "Breakdown", the protagonist Dr. Shaun Murphy (played by Freddie Highmore) confronts the new Chief of Surgery, Dr. Jackson Han (played by Daniel Dae Kim), after learning Dr. Han is transferring him from Surgery to Pathology against Shaun's wishes due to Dr. Han's bigotry against autistic people despite Shaun and his co-workers proving to Dr. Han that Shaun is a great and smart doctor despite his autism. When Dr. Han still refuses to reverse his decision, Shaun has a breakdown, angrily telling Dr. Han, "[b]I am a Surgeon![/b]" repeatedly.

The scene became a popular meme in 2023 on TikTok due to how over the top Freddie Highmore's acting in that clip. Furthermore, due to many not understanding the scene out-of-context, many sided with Dr. Han, believing he had the right to remove Dr. Shaun from Surgery due to the latter's immature reaction, not realizing that Dr. Han was the antagonist and unfairly removed Dr. Shaun from Surgery due to Dr. Han's bigotry against autistic people.

[b]Rei no pool[/b] (例のプール, lit. "the usual pool"), officially called the[b] Hanazono Room[/b], is that indoor swimming [[pool]] with angled solarium windows which can be seen in just about every pool-related Japanese adult video ever.

It is located on the top floor of a building in [[Shinjuku (tokyo)|]], and was formerly part of a private penthouse apartment during the area's economic boom. It's now owned by a company that rents locations for video shoots. Surprisingly for a studio frequently used to film porn, it overlooks an elementary school.

The pool virtually ceased being available for JAV shoots in 2020 due to the rising cost of facility maintenance expenses to clean up afterwards. The pool remains open for non-AV shoots such as gravure and non-pornographic shoots.

Despite its reputation as a common location for JAVs, the pool has recently been featured in a handful of mainstream productions as well, including an episode of [i][[Kamen Rider Fourze (Series)|Kamen Rider Fourze]][/i].

title: call_of_duty:_world_at_war
body:
A first-person shooter [[video game]] developed by [[Treyarch]] and published by [[Activision]]. The game was released in November 2008 and is the fifth installment in the [[Call of Duty]] franchise. World at War is set during [[World War II]] and features both single-player and multiplayer modes.

The single-player campaign mostly follows the perspectives of two different Allied soldiers: Private Miller of the [[United States Marine Corps]] and Private Dimitri Petrenko of the [[Soviet Army]]. The game's story takes place in the Pacific and Eastern Front theaters of World War II, with players fighting against Japanese and German forces.

It was also the first game to introduce the [[zombie|Zombies]] gamemode, formerly known as Nazi Zombies during the game's lifespan.

World at War was generally well-received by critics and fans, with many praising the game's gritty depiction of World War II and its intense gameplay.

title: kurt_cobain
body:
An American musician, best known as the lead singer, guitarist, and primary songwriter of the rock band [[nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]. Born on February 20, 1967, in Aberdeen, Washington, he started playing music at a young age. In 1987, he formed Nirvana with bassist [[Krist Novoselic]], with drummer [[Dave Grohl]] eventually joining in 1990, after a succession of a few others in the position.

Nirvana's second album, "[[Nevermind]]," was released in 1991 and featured the hit single "Smells Like Teen Spirit," which helped to popularize the grunge music genre. Despite his success, Cobain struggled with drug addiction, chronic pain, and depression throughout his life, and tragically died by suicide on April 5, 1994, at the age of 27.

h4. External links

title: demon_days_(gorillaz)
body:
The second studio album by the British virtual band Gorillaz, released in 2005. The album features a diverse range of musical styles, including alternative rock, hip-hop, electronic, and pop, and features collaborations with a number of high-profile artists, including De La Soul, MF Doom, Neneh Cherry, and Ike Turner.

The album is known for its dark, apocalyptic themes and commentary on modern society, with lyrics that address topics such as war, politics, and consumer culture. The album's sound is characterized by its use of electronic beats, samples, and synthesizers, as well as the distinctive vocal style of Gorillaz frontman Damon Albarn.

"Demon Days" was a critical and commercial success upon its release, and has since become one of the band's most popular and well-regarded albums. It features several hit singles, including "Feel Good Inc.", "DARE", and "Dirty Harry", and was nominated for several awards, including the Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album.

It is also a source for parodies based off [[album cover redraw|album cover redraws]].

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Demon Days":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demon_Days]

title: karn_(metal_slug)
body:
One of the Bosses from [[Metal Slug]], Specifically from Metal Slug 1 and Metal Slug X.

Karn is one of the pair of super-heavy tanks (the other one is Shoe, its twin.)  created by the Rebel Army for cooperative mission. They are each armed with one main turret-mounted cannon, two sub-cannon turrets on the front, and a missile launcher on the back. Two side-mounted hatches allow soldiers to help defend the tank as well, usually with bazookas or rocket launchers.

In the game itself, Karn fires an HE cannon and HEAT Rounds from its sub turrets, combined with a Rocket Howitzer launching from its rear. The differences is Karn is using a darker or lighter color than Shoe, while the rest of its armaments are identical.

title: kagurazaki_shizuki
body:
An [[original]] character by [[Rakurakutei Ramen]]. 

Though she has the form of a young human girl, she's actually a [[fox]] youkai who's roughly 330 years old. Normally she wears common [[miko]] clothing (from serving the Kagurazaki miko family for generations) along with her yellowish [[blonde hair]] and [[red eyes]]. She is prone to entering "half-demon form," however, by popping her [[fox tail|tail]][[multiple tails|(s)]], [[claws]], and [[fox ears|ears]] whenever emotional or agitated. 

Often seen with [[ujikintoki tamaryu|Tamaryu]] and later [[ran straherz|Ran]], having her crush on the former expand into outright polygynous engagement with the whole love triangle.

After being tapped by the Kuuko [[Saiguuji Sachi|Sachi]] to be a successor in the "Holy Trio" (as "Radiant Heaven Mikoko") of youkai along with Tamaryu and Ran, she finally stopped lazing about in her studies, and learned how to use her fox youkai illusion magic transform into an adult.

In her adult form, she has long, straight [[black hair]] and keeps her red eyes while still usually wearing her miko outfit.  She also develops a bust that Tamaryu sometimes violently [[breast envy|envies]].  

Shizuki uses her adult form to signify her occupying her role as a teacher, and changes back to a child as soon as she's doing anything for personal reasons.

title: american-180
body:
The [b]American-180[/b] is a .22 calibre [b][[submachine gun]][/b] of US origin, developed in the 1960s. The [[weapon]] externally resembles the [[thompson submachine gun|Thompson]], either with a straight handguard or wooden [[vertical foregrip]]. It uses a top-loaded pan magazine with massive capacity, ranging from 165 to 275 .22 LR rounds. 
Its high rate of fire can rupture soft [[bulletproof vest]]s due to cumulative damage despite the cartridge lacking stopping power and sufficient velocity.
